From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 21:50:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: drain Fruit Jam usbhost RX tail after EOP

The RX EOP detector can report packet completion before the decoder has pushed
the last few bytes into the RX FIFO.  The first bounded drain only waited when
the packet looked completely empty, which let longer self-RX packets truncate
at EOP.  Keep draining until the FIFO has stayed quiet briefly after EOP, still
with a hard bound so a broken packet cannot spin in the kernel.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 17 +++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -1137,14 +1137,19 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_receive_raw(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh, bool ack_data
 			break;
 		}
 		if (irq & FJ_PIO_IRQ_RX_EOP) {
-			u32 drain_waited;
+			u32 drain_waited, quiet;
 
-			for (drain_waited = 0; !len && drain_waited < 50;
-			     drain_waited++) {
+			for (drain_waited = 0, quiet = 0;
+			     drain_waited < 50 && quiet < 8; drain_waited++) {
+				u32 before = len;
+
 				FJ_USBHOST_DRAIN_RX_FIFO();
-				if (len)
-					break;
-				udelay(1);
+				if (len == before)
+					quiet++;
+				else
+					quiet = 0;
+				if (quiet < 8)
+					udelay(1);
 			}
 			ret = len ? 0 : -ENODATA;
 			break;
